50|$|A <b>de{{leverage}}d</b> floating-rate note is one {{bearing a}} coupon {{that is the}} product of the index and a leverage factor, where the leverage factor is between zero and one. A <b>deleveraged</b> floater, which gives the investor decreased exposure to the underlying index, can be replicated by buying a pure FRN and entering into a swap to pay floating and receive fixed, on a notional amount of less than the face value of the FRN.|$|R
